TinyEMU 9p: clamp client msize to the fixed buffer capacity (8192).

The version handler set s->msize to the client's requested msize with no
clamp; TinyEMU's Tread/Treaddir responses use fixed buffers sized for the
default 8192. A client mounting with a larger msize (e.g. msize=131072)
overruns those buffers and hangs the guest on the first real read while the
small attach/getattr ops during mount still succeed. Clamp to 8192.

--- a/virtio.c
+++ b/virtio.c
@@ -2456,9 +2456,14 @@
         {
             uint32_t msize;
             char *version;
-            if (unmarshall(s, queue_idx, desc_idx, &offset, 
+            if (unmarshall(s, queue_idx, desc_idx, &offset,
                            "ws", &msize, &version))
                 goto protocol_error;
+            /* tug: clamp to our fixed 9p buffer capacity. Accepting a larger
+             * client-requested msize overruns the fixed Tread/Treaddir response
+             * buffers and hangs the guest on the first real read. */
+            if (msize > 8192)
+                msize = 8192;
             s->msize = msize;
             //            printf("version: msize=%d version=%s\n", msize, version);
             free(version);
